SIMPLE: coke
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coke
<hw>Coke</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perh. akin to
<ets>cake</ets>, n.]</ety> <def>Mineral coal charred, or depriver of its
bitumen, sulphur, or other volatile matter by roasting in a kiln or
oven, or by distillation, as in gas works. It is largely used where a
smokeless fire is required.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>coak</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gas coke</b></col>, <cd>the coke formed in gas retorts,
as distinguished from that made in ovens.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Coke
<hw>Coke</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To convert into coke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cokenay</ent>⟦br⟧
